The first Marsh Athlete of the Month has been decided after receiving more than 300,000 votes. And the winners are ... 
Alex Buck of Pendleton Heights and Tyrone Tracy from Decatur Central. 
Buck was named athlete of the week for the week ending Sept. 19 after winning the Flashrock Invitational with a time of 18:09. There were 143,652 votes for the female Athlete of the Month and Buck edged Ellie Wilson of Greenwood Christian Academy by just 1,498. Buck finished with a total of 50,783 votes. 
Tracy earned athlete of the week honors for the week ending Sept. 7 after carrying the ball seven times for 130 yards and 2 touchdowns and catching three passes for 117 yards and 2 more scores in Decatur Central's 49-14 victory over Martinsville. Tracy dominated the voting, picking up 93,818 out of the 161,241 cast on the male side. 
The Marsh Athlete of the Month is part of the IndyStar's new Indiana Sports Awards program , a multi-faceted program to bring state-wide recognition to high school athletes and sports in Indiana. To be eligible for Athlete of the Month, an athletic department representative has to nominate an athlete for Athlete of the Week with The Star picking a winner in each sport.
